edback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">März 22, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xwv1665702674089.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xwv1665702674089.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xwv1665702674089.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xwv1665702674089\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">This section of the initialization file records the state of certain UPI objects when\n      the user exits an application.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xwv1665702674089__section_w3297ab1b5b1_w3298ab1b5_w3299ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d621070e50\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xwv1665702674089__p_d145877e1_d145878e1_d145879e1\">All settings in this section are automatically updated by Uniface whenever it terminates.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"xwv1665702674089__note_w3309ab1b5b1b5_w3310ab1b5b1_w3311ab1b5_w3312ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> On Windows, the information is recorded in the Registry.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xwv1665702674089__section_w3300ab1b5b3_w3301ab1b5_w3302ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d621070e62\">Settings</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"xwv1665702674089__table_d17795e1_d17796e1_d17797e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">State Information</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xwv1665702674089__table_d17795e1_d17796e1_d17797e1__entry__1\">Setting</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xwv1665702674089__table_d17795e1_d17796e1_d17797e1__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwv1665702674089__table_d17795e1_d17796e1_d17797e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword option\">GFPPALETTE</span>= <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>\n                        | <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwv1665702674089__table_d17795e1_d17796e1_d17797e1__entry__2\">Visibility of the Tool Palette within the\n                        Uniface IDE. The default is <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code> (true).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwv1665702674089__table_d17795e1_d17796e1_d17797e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword option\">GFPSTATUS</span>= <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>\n                        | <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwv1665702674089__table_d17795e1_d17796e1_d17797e1__entry__2\">Visibility of the Status Box within the Uniface\n                        IDE. The default is <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwv1665702674089__table_d17795e1_d17796e1_d17797e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword option\">PANEL</span>= <code class=\"ph codeph\">on</code> |\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">off</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwv1665702674089__table_d17795e1_d17796e1_d17797e1__entry__2\">Visibility of the session panel and the\n                        toolbar. These can be displayed or hidden at run time using the Panel...\n                        command on the application panel, or with GOLD+X . The default is\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">on</code>. To control the contents of the Uniface toolbar use\n                        the settings in the [toolbar] section. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qjq1665702674162.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qjq1665702674162.html\" title=\"The [toolbar] section of the initialization file controls the content of the Uniface toolbar, which is available for all Uniface client/server applications. All settings in this section are automatically updated by Uniface whenever it terminates.\">[toolbar]</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwv1665702674089__table_d17795e1_d17796e1_d17797e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword option\">PANELMIN</span>= <code class=\"ph codeph\">on</code>\n                        | <code class=\"ph codeph\">off</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwv1665702674089__table_d17795e1_d17796e1_d17797e1__entry__2\">Records whether the panel was last minimized or\n                        not. The default is <code class=\"ph codeph\">off</code>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwv1665702674089__table_d17795e1_d17796e1_d17797e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword option\">PANELPOS</span>=\n                           <var class=\"keyword varname\">x,y</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwv1665702674089__table_d17795e1_d17796e1_d17797e1__entry__2\">Coordinates of the floating session panel;\n                           <var class=\"keyword varname\">x</var> is the horizontal position, <var class=\"keyword varname\">y</var> is\n                        vertical position. This setting is only used if the panel position in the\n                        application shell form is set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">default</code>. The default is\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">0,0</code>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwv1665702674089__table_d17795e1_d17796e1_d17797e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword option\">PANELSIZE</span>=\n                           <var class=\"keyword varname\">h,w</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwv1665702674089__table_d17795e1_d17796e1_d17797e1__entry__2\">Dimensions of the floating session panel. The\n                        default is <code class=\"ph codeph\">0,0</code>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwv1665702674089__table_d17795e1_d17796e1_d17797e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword option\">WINDOWMAX</span>= <code class=\"ph codeph\">on</code>\n                        | <code class=\"ph codeph\">off</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwv1665702674089__table_d17795e1_d17796e1_d17797e1__entry__2\">Determines the initial state of the application\n                        window (using the entire screen or not). The default is\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">off</code>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwv1665702674089__table_d17795e1_d17796e1_d17797e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword option\">WINDOWPOS</span>=\n                           <var class=\"keyword varname\">x,y</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwv1665702674089__table_d17795e1_d17796e1_d17797e1__entry__2\">Coordinates of the application window as a\n                        horizontal position, vertical position pair. The default is the default\n                        Microsoft Windows position.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwv1665702674089__table_d17795e1_d17796e1_d17797e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword option\">WINDOWSIZE</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwv1665702674089__table_d17795e1_d17796e1_d17797e1__entry__2\">Determines the initial size of the application\n                        window. The application window can be resized at run time. The values should\n                        be supplied as a pair of width, height values. The default is the default\n                        Microsoft Windows window size.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533960\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533960\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "[state] Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 22, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 This section of the initialization file records the state of certain UPI objects when the user exits an application. Description All settings in this section are automatically updated by Uniface whenever it terminates. Note: On Windows, the information is recorded in the Registry. Settings Table 1. State Information Setting Description GFPPALETTE = 0 | 1 Visibility of the Tool Palette within the Uniface IDE. The default is 1 (true). GFPSTATUS = 0 | 1 Visibility of the Status Box within the Uniface IDE. The default is 1 . PANEL = on | off Visibility of the session panel and the toolbar. These can be displayed or hidden at run time using the Panel... command on the application panel, or with GOLD+X . The default is on . To control the contents of the Uniface toolbar use the settings in the [toolbar] section. For more information, see [toolbar] . PANELMIN = on | off Records whether the panel was last minimized or not. The default is off . PANELPOS = x,y Coordinates of the floating session panel; x is the horizontal position, y is vertical position. This setting is only used if the panel position in the application shell form is set to default . The default is 0,0 . PANELSIZE = h,w Dimensions of the floating session panel. The default is 0,0 . WINDOWMAX = on | off Determines the initial state of the application window (using the entire screen or not). The default is off . WINDOWPOS = x,y Coordinates of the application window as a horizontal position, vertical position pair. The default is the default Microsoft Windows position. WINDOWSIZE Determines the initial size of the application window. The application window can be resized at run time. The values should be supplied as a pair of width, height values. The default is the default Microsoft Windows window size. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}